# Smart Traffic IoT Project

Smart City: Traffic Junction Monitoring & Safety Analytics

## Features Implemented ✅

- [x] 5 sensor types (vehicle count, speed, rain, light, pollution)
- [x] Configurable frequency & dispatch rates (YAML)
- [x] 2 simulated junctions (A, B)
- [x] Virtual fog nodes per junction (FastAPI)
- [x] Rolling 10-second aggregation
- [x] Real-time event detection (speeding, congestion, incidents)
- [x] AWS SQS queues (FIFO, DLQ)
- [x] Lambda functions (process aggregates, events, API)
- [x] DynamoDB tables (aggregates, events, KPIs)
- [x] React dashboard with live charts
- [x] API Gateway endpoints
- [x] S3 + CloudFront hosting
- [x] Terraform IaC (all AWS services)
- [x] GitHub Actions CI/CD
- [x] Unit & integration tests
- [x] Load test (500 events/sec, 30 sec)
- [x] Failure tests (DLQ, retry logic)
- [x] Complete documentation (25+ pages)
- [x] 4-minute demo script

## Project Structure

```
smart-traffic-iot/
├── sensors/               # Simulator engine
├── fog/                  # FastAPI fog node
├── cloud/lambdas/        # Lambda functions
├── cloud/terraform/      # IaC
├── dashboard/            # React UI
├── tests/               # Test suite
├── docs/                # Documentation
├── .github/workflows/   # CI/CD
└── docker-compose.yml   # Local stack
```

## Deployment

### Local
```bash
docker-compose up
# Dashboard: ${REACT_APP_DASHBOARD_URL}
```

### AWS
```bash
cd cloud/terraform
terraform init && terraform apply
```

