## Key Metrics

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Sensor types | 5 (count, speed, rain, light, pollution) |
| Junctions | 2 (A, B) |
| Ingestion rate | 1,000 events/sec (burst) |
| Fog aggregation | 10-sec rolling windows |
| Bandwidth reduction | 80% (aggregates vs raw) |
| Event detection algorithms | 3 (speeding, congestion, incident) |
| Cloud services | 9 (SQS, Lambda, DynamoDB, API Gateway, S3, CloudFront, IAM, CloudWatch, Terraform) |
| Lambda functions | 3 (process aggregates, events, API) |
| DynamoDB tables | 3 (aggregates, events, KPIs) |
| Dashboard update frequency | 3 seconds |
| Test coverage | Unit + integration + load + failure |

## Scalability

- Fog: Local analytics, real-time detection
- SQS: Decouples fog from cloud, absorbs bursts (15,000+ messages)
- Lambda: Auto-scales to 1000+ concurrent
- DynamoDB: On-demand billing
- Dashboard: CloudFront CDN + S3

## Resilience

- Deduplication: 10-sec eventId cache + SQS content dedup
- Idempotency: Unique keys prevent duplicate processing
- DLQ: Failed messages quarantined (max 3 retries)
- Retry: Exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s)
- Monitoring: CloudWatch metrics + logs

## Testing

```bash
# Unit tests
pytest tests/test_fog_analytics.py -v

# Integration tests
pytest tests/test_integration.py -v

# Load test (500 evt/sec)
bash tests/load_test.sh

# Failure test (DLQ)
bash tests/dlq_test.sh
```

